<subSubSection id="02A2651CFFBB760D3B92127DE7C9DBD3" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBB760D3B92127DE7C9DBD3" blockId="11.[151,1437,1386,2032]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBB760D3B92127DE377DB74" bold="true" box="[198,319,1580,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Recognized by the distinctively long, dense, erect or suberect, deep brown simple setae covering the dorsal surface of the body (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBB760D39381202E094DB5F" box="[620,732,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D39FA1202E094DB5F" box="[686,732,1619,1645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="6.7">6, 7</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBB760D39BC1202E17CDB5F" box="[744,820,1619,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D39BC1202E17CDB5F" box="[744,820,1619,1645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="39.4">39, 40</number>
</figureCitation>
), the shining sericeous setae densely scattered on the proximal 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D3A58122BE353DBA6" box="[268,283,1658,1684]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D3A71122BE37ADBA6" box="[293,306,1658,1684]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.0">3</number>
of hemelytron, the yellow-brown hemelytron, the castaneous head, pronotum and scutellum. Most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8DB84D14FFBB760D3A3412F0E061DB88" authority="Kulik" authorityName="Kulik" box="[352,553,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pherolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplus">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBB760D3A3412F0E391DB88" box="[352,473,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">P. amplus</emphasis>
Kulik
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBB760D396F12F1E0FCDB88" box="[571,692,1696,1722]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D39D712F1E0FCDB88" box="[643,692,1696,1722]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="3.4">3, 4</number>
</figureCitation>
) in size and coloration of dorsum, but distinguished by the structure of male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBB760D3A8D1296E02FDBD3" box="[473,615,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D39481296E02FDBD3" box="[540,615,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="45.0" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="43.0">43–47</number>
</figureCitation>
) and the presence of extremely long simple setae (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBB760D3FEC1296E73DDBD3" box="[1208,1397,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D3FAE1296E73DDBD3" box="[1274,1397,1735,1761]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="38.695" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="37.39">37, 39–40</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02A2651CFFBB760B3B9112BCE0D3DAF0" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBB760D3B9112BCE1F8DA3A" blockId="11.[151,1437,1386,2032]" box="[197,944,1773,1800]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBB760D3B9112BCE31EDA35" bold="true" box="[197,342,1773,1799]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Description</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBB760D3A3112BFE3E9DA35" box="[357,417,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBB760D3AE512BFE3B2DA3A" box="[433,506,1774,1800]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Fig. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBB760D3ABC12BFE3B2DA3A" box="[488,506,1774,1800]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
): Macropterous, oval, medium-sized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBB760D3B911345E644DAC2" blockId="11.[151,1437,1386,2032]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Coloration: General coloration yellowish brown or brown, without distinctive colored markings on dorsum; head, pronotum, exposed part of mesoscutum and scutellum castaneous to almost black; membrane fumose, without spots; eyes dark brown with outer margin reddish; antennal segment I and proximal half of segment II dirty yellow, distal half yellow-brown to castaneous, segment III and IV castaneous to black; clypeus and buccula reddish brown; labium yellowish brown; coxae and trochanter pale-yellow, femora and tibiae pale-brown, tarsal segment III blackish brown; abdomen dark brown.</paragraph>
<caption id="1EC7661FFFBC760A3BC313C7E356DAC1" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" targetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBC760A3BC313C7E356DAC1" blockId="12.[151,1437,1942,2035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBC760A3BC313C7E316DA9C" bold="true" box="[151,350,1942,1966]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">FIGURES 37–42.</emphasis>
Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of 
<taxonomicName id="8DB84D14FFBC760A3F5E13C6E6C7DA9C" box="[1034,1167,1943,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pherolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipilus">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBC760A3F5E13C6E6C7DA9C" box="[1034,1167,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">P. longipilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41–42. Parempodia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="1EC7661FFFBD760B3BC317F1E7C6DEE8" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" targetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBD760B3BC317F1E7C6DEE8" blockId="13.[151,1436,928,986]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B3BC317F1E314DE8A" bold="true" box="[151,348,928,952]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">FIGURES 43–48.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8DB84D14FFBD760B3A3717F1E00EDE85" box="[355,582,928,951]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pherolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipilus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B3A3717F1E00EDE85" box="[355,582,928,951]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Pherolepis 
<taxonomicName id="8DB84D14FFBD760B3A8F17F1E00EDE85" box="[475,582,928,951]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species" species="longipilus" status="sp. nov.">longipilus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B391817F1E0E9DE8A" bold="true" box="[588,673,928,952]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="63FF57FEFFBD760B391817F1E0E9DE8A" box="[588,673,928,952]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: 43–47. Male genitalia (scale=0.10mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale=0.20mm), dorsal view
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBD760B3B911059E291D95D" blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Surface and Vestiture: Dorsal surface of body covered densely with two 
<typeStatus id="95038835FFBD760B3F661059E639D910" box="[1074,1137,1032,1058]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">types</typeStatus>
of setae, distinctly long, erect or suberect, simple setae (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B3943107EE09FD97B" box="[535,727,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3908107EE09FD97B" box="[604,727,1071,1097]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="38.695" valueMax="40.0" valueMin="37.39">37, 39–40</number>
</figureCitation>
) and decumbent or appressed, flattened, shining sericeous setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBD760B3B92102DE14DDB81" blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Structure: 
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B3A13102DE3CED9A7" box="[327,390,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B3AC8102DE3B2D9A4" box="[412,506,1148,1174]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 42" captionStartId="12.[151,270,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[184,1409,197,1908]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 42. Scanning electron micrographs of morphological structures of P. longipilus (male): 37. Lateral view of head; 38. Scent-gland evaporatory area; 39. Simple setae on scutellum; 40. Simple setae on hemelytron. 41 – 42. Parempodia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191194/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3A8D102DE3B2D9A4" box="[473,506,1148,1174]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="37.0">37</number>
</figureCitation>
): Triangular in frontal view and transverse in dorsal view, weakly convex posteriorly; vertex and frons moderately inclined, densely covered with two 
<typeStatus id="95038835FFBD760B3F7510F2E617D98F" box="[1057,1119,1187,1213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">types</typeStatus>
of setae mentioned above, posterior margin of vertex forming a complete, weakly rounded carina; frons and clypeus distinctly protrudent, easily visible in dorsal view; mandibular and maxillary plates, and buccula covered with sparse, recumbent, simple setae; labium elongate, almost reaching posterior margin of hind trochanter; eyes broadly ovoid; antennal segment I short and stout, narrow at base, segment II long, tubular and weakly curved; segment III equal to segment IV in diameter and length, more slender than segment II. 
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B3FEA1135E75DD84F" box="[1214,1301,1380,1405]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum broad, weakly tumidiform, anterior and posterior lobes not demarcated, posterolateral angles rounded, posterior margin slightly concave; mesoscutum broadly exposed, weakly declining; scutellum slightly swollen mesially; hemelytron broad, clavus weakly elevated along the claval commissure; cuneus broadly triangular, moderately declining; veins of membrane indistinct; femora stout and somewhat flattened, tibiae cylindrical and straight, with two rows of black short spicules; tarsal segment I and II subequal in length, segment III about two times length of segment II; claws distinctly curved, slightly broadened basally, pulvilli absent, parempodia lamellate, recurved, and convergent apically. 
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B38931222E673DBBE" box="[967,1083,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Relatively stout and broad, generally covered with recumbent, pale simple setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBD760B3B911291E020DA7C" blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B3AD61291E05FDBE8" box="[386,535,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3A931291E05FDBE8" box="[455,535,1728,1754]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="45.0" valueMax="47.0" valueMin="43.0">43–47</number>
</figureCitation>
): Vesica typically L-shaped, with a large, flattened, spinelike projection on shaft, near apex with a fingerlike process, apex of vesica with broad membrane (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B3F1A12B6E6EEDA33" box="[1102,1190,1767,1793]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3FD112B6E6EEDA33" box="[1157,1190,1767,1793]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
); left paramere boatshaped, hypophysis elongate, sensory lobe blunt (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B39B6135CE13ADA15" box="[738,882,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Figs. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3871135CE13ADA15" box="[805,882,1805,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="44.45">44, 45</number>
</figureCitation>
); right paramere leaflike (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B3FF2135CE6B7DA15" box="[1190,1279,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3F8A135CE6B7DA15" box="[1246,1279,1805,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="46.0">46</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallotheca elongate, apex weakly curved (
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B39571365E013DA7C" box="[515,603,1844,1870]" captionStart="FIGURES 43 – 48" captionStartId="13.[151,269,928,952]" captionTargetBox="[236,1424,218,891]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,194,904]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 43 – 48. Pherolepis longipilus sp. nov.: 43 – 47. Male genitalia (scale = 0.10 mm): 43. Vesica; 44. Left paramere; 45. Left paramere, apical view; 46. Right paramere; 47. Phallotheca. 48. Female genitalia (scale = 0.20 mm), dorsal view" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191195/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B396E1365E013DA7C" box="[570,603,1844,1870]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBD760B3B91130AE371DAAE" blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="78CCEA85FFBD760B3B91130AE355DA46" box="[197,285,1883,1908]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="D2832A12FFBD760B3A79130AE33FDA47" box="[301,375,1883,1909]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,272,1818,1842]" captionTargetBox="[343,1230,403,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[340,1248,390,1792]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus views of Pherolepis spp. 1. aenescens (male); 2. aenescens (female); 3. amplus (male); 4. amplus (female); 5. kiritshenkoi (male); 6. longipilus (male); 7. longipilus (female); 8. nigrinus (male); 9. nigrinus (female); 10. robustus (male); 11. robustus (female)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/191188/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Fig. 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B3A31130AE33FDA47" box="[357,375,1883,1909]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
): Macropterous. Surface and coloration similar to male, the size weakly bigger than male, body broader.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A073697FFBD760B3B9113F9E0D3DAF0" blockId="13.[151,1438,1032,2025]" box="[197,667,1960,1986]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Female genitalia: Structure as figure 
<number id="FC7024B0FFBD760B392213F9E0DFDAF0" box="[630,663,1960,1986]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" value="48.0">48</number>
.
</paragraph>
